{"parentUuid":"f13f4df8-a6c7-4ec6-951c-48186131df57","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/nick/work/libnn","sessionId":"db819759-7330-4691-9a7b-4f3b80a8d38f","version":"2.1.72","gitBranch":"develop","slug":"velvety-questing-llama","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01HUFGqaBXacEGH5y15kTbqj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Yes — with a no-python GDB, the basic commands are:\n\n```gdb\n# Load ELF (symbols + section info)\nfile path/to/your.elf\n\n# If connecting to a remote target (JTAG/OpenOCD/GDB server):\ntarget remote <host>:<port>\nload                          # download sections to target memory\n\n# Or for a simulator:\ntarget sim\nload\nrun\n```\n\nKey commands without Python:\n\n| Command | What it does |\n|---------|-------------|\n| `file <elf>` | Load ELF symbols and section layout |\n| `load` | Transfer loadable sections to target |\n| `restore <bin> binary 0x80000000` | Load a raw binary at a specific address |\n| `set $pc = 0x80000000` | Set program counter manually |\n| `symbol-file <elf>` | Load only symbols (no sections) |\n| `add-symbol-file <elf> 0xADDR` | Load symbols with offset |\n\nIf you're working with the AX45MPV FPGA board, it's likely something like:\n\n```gdb\ntarget remote sw-boards.andestech.com:1116\nfile your_test.elf\nload\ncontinue\n```\n\nAre you trying to debug a specific test on the FPGA, or is this for a different setup?"}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":435,"cache_read_input_tokens":20711,"output_tokens":455,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":435,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZRCDcdddwLcYchvj2sNb","type":"assistant","uuid":"13f4226b-409d-4c94-9b26-0b69c0ce5e92","timestamp":"2026-03-26T06:10:12.951Z"}
